I"µ<h1 id="sota-guide---buzzard-knob-w4gng-021">SOTA Guide - Buzzard Knob, W4G/NG-021</h1>

<p>Note: Buzzard Knob is also accessible via Charlies Creek Rd and Blue Ridge Gap.  See my Hightower Bald guide for access to Blue Ridge Gap via Charlies Creek Rd.</p>

<h4 id="drive-guide---buzzard-knob-and-little-bald-knob-double-header">Drive Guide - Buzzard Knob and Little Bald Knob Double-header</h4>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Duration</strong>: 2:00</li>
  <li><strong>Google Maps</strong> URL from Ashford Dunwoody Rd and I-285 at 33.917, -84.3378: http://goo.gl/maps/9CYiQ</li>
  <li><strong>Seasonal/Limited Access</strong>: Paved road all the way.  Parking may be a problem on weekends.</li>
  <li><strong>Directions</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li>I-285</li>
      <li>I-85 N</li>
      <li>I-985/US-23 N and go 75.5</li>
      <li>In Clayton, L on US-76/GA-2 and go 16</li>
      <li>Paved Parking on R</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Food</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Last McDonalds: Clayton</li>
      <li>Penultimate McDonalds: Cornelia, on Level Grove Rd.
        <ul>
          <li>It comes just BEFORE Cornelia and your exit to US-441.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Notes</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>You cannot reach Cowart Gap via Mr. Bert Road in a passenger vehicle.  You may be able to reach it via ATV.  Road becomes  a wide trail by the time it reaches Cowart Gap.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h4 id="trail-guide">Trail Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Durations (Buzzard, then Little Bald 2013)</strong>: 3:00 - 3.5 Miles total, but it includes significant bushwhack.
    <ul>
      <li>2:30 - 3.3 miles, Dicks Creek Gap to Buzzard Knob. 1100â€™ total climb + 400â€™ dip to Cowart Gap. Medium-difficulty bushwhack in summer.</li>
      <li>2:00 - 2.1 miles, Buzzard Knob to Little Bald Knob. Cowart Gap to summit is 3/4 mile and 500â€™ climb.  Tough bushwhack in summer.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Durations (Little Bald, then Buzzard 2014)</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li>1:15 - Parking to Little Bald</li>
      <li>1:30 - On summit, Little Bald Knob</li>
      <li>1:45 - Little Bald Knob to Buzzard Knob</li>
      <li>1:15 - On summit, Buzzard Knob</li>
      <li>1:50 - Buzzard Knob to parking</li>
      <li>Note: This was so fast that I hurt a <strong>lot</strong> afterward.  Take more rest breaks and donâ€™t push so hard the next time.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Navigation</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Follow the AT blazes.</li>
      <li>Bushwhack to Buzzard from N34.93261 W83.60191</li>
      <li>Bushwhack to Little Bald from N34.91090 W83.60449 or N34.91260 W83.60179 and I donâ€™t like either one.
        <ul>
          <li>I went up from the second and down to the first in September 2013.  Miserable.</li>
          <li>I went up from the first and down from the second in January 2014. Hike up the hill was strenuous, but bushwhack was easier with winter die-off.  The bushwhack down wasnâ€™t too bad.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Trailhead altitude</strong>: 2675â€™ at Dicks Creek Gap</li>
  <li><strong>Summit altitude</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li>Little Bald Knob: 3460â€™</li>
      <li>Buzzard Knob: 3740â€™</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>GPS tracks/waypoints</strong>:
    <ul>
      <li>Dicks Creek Gap Trailhead: 34.91201, -83.61855</li>
      <li>Little Bald Knob: 34.9133, -83.6041</li>
      <li>Buzzard Knob: 34.9335, -83.6025</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h4 id="summit-guide">Summit Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li>Hang antenna from tree: Heavy vegetation makes it challenging.</li>
  <li>Space to guy mast: Heavy vegetation makes it challenging.</li>
  <li>Cell coverage: Good. AT&amp;T had 3G internet. VZN SMS good. No APRS msgs or beacons worked.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="scouting-after-hike">Scouting After Hike</h4>

<ul>
